Willard Louis https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Willard_Louis 0 Willard Louis (April 19, 1882 – July 22, 1926) was an American stage and film actor of the silent era. He appeared in 81 films between 1911 and 1926. He was born in San Francisco, California, and died in Glendale, California from a combination of typhoid fever and pneumonia, aged 44.
